== History == Suwa Shrine is believed to have been founded in {{ill|1390|ja|1390年}} ({{ill|Meitoku|ja|明徳}} 1){{sfn|Edo Meisho Zue|1927|p=591}}. It was established by Umehonbo Jokan, the bettō (chief priest) of the nearby {{ill|Kitano Shrine (Bunkyo-ku)|ja|北野神社 (文京区)}}, who enshrined a spirit from {{ill|Suwa Taisha|ja|諏訪大社|1=Suwa-taisha}} in his birthplace, {{ill|Shinano Province|ja|信濃国}}, {{ill|Suwa District|ja|諏訪郡}}. Due to this connection, Suwa Shrine remains an auxiliary shrine of Kitano Shrine<ref name="shrine">Kazunori Uchiumi (ed.), "Bunkyo-ku Jinja-shi," Bunkyo Ward Shrine General Assembly, 1988, pp. 39-40, 401-403</ref>.
== Sessha and Massha (Subordinate Shrines) == * Inari Shrine (Deity: {{ill|Ukanomitama|ja|倉稲魂命}})
== Access == *7-minute walk from {{ill|Korakuen Station|ja|後楽園駅}} Exit 1 ({{OSM経路図|start=35.70707,139.75158|goal=35.70686,139.74547|name=Route Guide}}).
