{{Infobox shrine | name = Suwa Shrine (諏訪神社) | image = [[File:Suwa-jinja (Bunkyo-ku).jpg|300px]] | location = {{ill|Tokyo|ja|東京都}}, {{ill|Bunkyo|ja|文京区}}, {{ill|Koraku|ja|後楽}} 2-18-18 | coordinates = | deity = {{ill|Takeminakata|ja|建御名方彦神別命|1=Takeminakata Hikokamiwake no Mikoto}}, {{ill|Yasakatome-no-kami|ja|八坂刀売神}} | founded = {{ill|1390|ja|1390th year }} ({{ill|Meitoku|ja|明徳}} 1) | alternate_names = Koishikawa Suwa Shrine (小石川諏訪神社) | festival = September 17 }}
'''Suwa Shrine''' (諏訪神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社}} in {{ill|Bunkyo|ja|文京区}}, {{ill|Tokyo|ja|東京都}}.
== History == Suwa Shrine is believed to have been founded in {{ill|1390|ja|1390th year }} ({{ill|Meitoku|ja|明徳}} 1){{sfn|Edo Meisho Zue|1927|p=591}}. It was established by Umehonbo Jokan, the bettō (chief priest) of the nearby {{ill|Kitano Shrine (Bunkyo-ku)|ja|北野神社 (文京区)}}, who enshrined a spirit from {{ill|Suwa Taisha|ja|諏訪大社|1=Suwa-taisha}} in his birthplace, {{ill|Shinano Province|ja|信濃国}}, {{ill|Suwa District|ja|諏訪郡}}. Due to this connection, Suwa Shrine remains an auxiliary shrine of Kitano Shrine<ref name="shrine">Kazunori Uchiumi (ed.), "Bunkyo-ku Jinja-shi," Bunkyo Ward Shrine General Assembly, 1988, pp. 39-40, 401-403</ref>.
== Sessha and Massha (Subordinate Shrines) == * Inari Shrine (Deity: {{ill|Ukanomitama|ja|倉稲魂命}})
== Access == *7-minute walk from {{ill|Korakuen Station|ja|後楽園駅}} Exit 1 ({{OSM経路図|start=35.70707,139.75158|goal=35.70686,139.74547|name=Route Guide}}).
== Notes == {{Reflist}}
== References == * Kazunori Uchiumi (ed.), "Bunkyo-ku Jinja-shi," Bunkyo Ward Shrine General Assembly, 1988. * {{cite book|title={{ill|Edo Meisho Zue|ja|江戸名所図会}}|id={{NDLJP|1174144/299}}|publisher=Yūhōdō Shoten|editor=Nagatoshi Saito|volume=2|series=Yūhōdō Bunko|year=1927|chapter=巻之四 天権之部 諏訪神社|pages=588-589,591|ref={{sfnref|Edo Meisho Zue|1927}}}}
