== History == Suwa Shrine is believed to have been founded in [[:en:1390|1390]] ([[:en:Meitoku|Meitoku]] 1){{sfn|Edo Meisho Zue|1927|p=591}}. It was established by Umehonbo Jokan, the bettō (chief priest) of the nearby {{ill|Kitano Shrine (Bunkyo-ku)|ja|北野神社 (文京区)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kitano Shrine (Bunkyo-ku)|qq=}}, who enshrined a spirit from [[:en:Suwa-taisha|Suwa-taisha]] in his birthplace, [[:en:Shinano Province|Shinano Province]], [[:en:Suwa District, Nagano|Suwa District]]. Due to this connection, Suwa Shrine remains an auxiliary shrine of Kitano Shrine<ref name="shrine">Kazunori Uchiumi (ed.), "Bunkyo-ku Jinja-shi," Bunkyo Ward Shrine General Assembly, 1988, pp. 39-40, 401-403</ref>.
== Sessha and Massha (Subordinate Shrines) == * Inari Shrine (Deity: {{ill|Ukanomitama|ja|倉稲魂命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ukanomitama|qq=}})
== Access == *7-minute walk from [[:en:Kōrakuen Station|Korakuen Station]] Exit 1 ({{OSM経路図|start=35.70707,139.75158|goal=35.70686,139.74547|name=Route Guide}}).
